<subpara id="RM000000XUF008X_z0" proc-id="RM0250U___00009NG00000">
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<step1>
<ptxt>READ DATA LIST</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Using the intelligent tester's DATA LIST allows switch, sensor, actuator and other item values to be read without removing any parts. Reading the DATA LIST relay in troubleshooting is one way to save time.</ptxt>
</atten4>
<step2>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Turn the engine switch on (IG). When the intelligent tester cannot be turned on due to a malfunction or other problem, refer to "precautions when using the intelligent tester" (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000XU6008X"/>).</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Enter the following menus: DIAGNOSIS / OBD/MOBD / DATA LIST.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Read the DATA LIST according to the display on the tester.</ptxt>
